<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="56" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
The lectotype has a handwritten label by Schrader &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. commutatus" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" rank="species" species="commutatus">B. commutatus</taxonomicName>
/ Fl. Germ. / 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Göttingen">Goettingen</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
&quot; and a handwritten indication as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“typus-material”">&quot;typus-material&quot;</normalizedToken>
. Currently, there is another label on this sheet by H.Scholz 1998 marking it as Neotypus, which was published in 
<bibRefCitation author="Scholz, H" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repertorium" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" pagination="425 - 438" refId="B27" refString="Scholz, H, 1999. Eine neue Unterart des Bromus secalinus (Gramineae) -ein Sekundaeres Unkraut. Feddes Repertorium 110 (5-6): 425 - 438" title="Eine neue Unterart des Bromus secalinus (Gramineae) - ein Sekundaeres Unkraut." volume="110" year="1999">Scholz (1999</bibRefCitation>
: 436). Although both publications fulfil the conditions for a formal typification of a lectotype or a neotype, the 
<bibRefCitation author="Acedo, C" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="B1" refString="Acedo, C, Llamas, F, 1999. The genus Bromus L. (Poaceae) in the Iberian Peninsula. Phaneogamarum Monographiae. J.Cramer, Berlin." title="The genus Bromus L. (Poaceae) in the Iberian Peninsula. Phaneogamarum Monographiae. J. Cramer, Berlin." year="1999">Acedo and Llamas (1999</bibRefCitation>
: 73) publication appeared in February and is probably the first typification (ICN, Art. 10. 5). There are two important facts to consider. First, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Kerguelen, M" journalOrPublisher="Lejeunia" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 343" refId="B17" refString="Kerguelen, M, 1975. Les Gramineae (Poaceae) de la Flore Francaise. Essai de mise au point taxonomique et nomenclaturale. Lejeunia 75: 1 - 343" title="Les Gramineae (Poaceae) de la Flore Francaise. Essai de mise au point taxonomique et nomenclaturale." volume="75" year="1975">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(1975
</bibRefCitation>
: 100), there is original material in GOET. We consulted that herbarium and found two sheets that Schrader sent to GFW Meyer, which are indeed original material. Both bear handwritten labels by Schrader. The first sheet label says &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. commutatus" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" rank="species" species="commutatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">B. commutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fl. Germ. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Göttingen”">Goettingen&quot;</normalizedToken>
and the second sheet label &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. commutatus" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" rank="species" species="commutatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">B. commutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fl. Germ. var. spic. paulo brevior. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Göttingen”">Goettingen&quot;</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
